00:56:59.410 --> 00:57:03.400
AUDIENCE: So I have a question
about advaita and non-duality,

00:57:03.400 --> 00:57:05.370
which I've been thinking
about for a long time.

00:57:05.370 --> 00:57:08.820
So if we are really
not separate,

00:57:08.820 --> 00:57:11.340
if there is only
one thing, then how

00:57:11.340 --> 00:57:14.610
do we reconcile that with
karma and reincarnation?

00:57:14.610 --> 00:57:16.590
What is the entity
that is reborn?

00:57:16.590 --> 00:57:18.900
What is the entity to
which karma attaches

00:57:18.900 --> 00:57:20.970
if there is no separation?

00:57:20.970 --> 00:57:24.870
SRI M: As long as there is an
ignorance of this understanding

00:57:24.870 --> 00:57:30.870
and experience, then all
these things are really real.

00:57:30.870 --> 00:57:32.490
Where does an entity separate?

00:57:32.490 --> 00:57:34.050
Where is the reincarnation?

00:57:34.050 --> 00:57:35.760
Everything is going on.

00:57:35.760 --> 00:57:38.910
The moment it is actually
understood and experienced

00:57:38.910 --> 00:57:42.090
that there is only one, then
there is no reincarnation,

00:57:42.090 --> 00:57:44.880
there is no nothing!

00:57:44.880 --> 00:57:49.290
It's the mind that
decide on this.

00:57:49.290 --> 00:57:53.040
You-- right now we are
living in this dream.

00:57:53.040 --> 00:57:57.690
And if anybody says this is
a dream, we won't believe it.

00:57:57.690 --> 00:58:01.830
Because in the
dream, all my dream,

00:58:01.830 --> 00:58:06.810
when we are chased by a tiger,
do we say this is a dream

00:58:06.810 --> 00:58:10.380
or do we run for our lives?

00:58:10.380 --> 00:58:12.360
I'm just giving you an example.

00:58:12.360 --> 00:58:14.790
Examples are not perfect.

00:58:14.790 --> 00:58:16.920
And when I come
out of the dream,

00:58:16.920 --> 00:58:20.130
I say, ah, this
was a great dream.

00:58:20.130 --> 00:58:22.440
I may still be sweating
and palpitating,

00:58:22.440 --> 00:58:25.330
but I say, oh, this was a dream.

00:58:25.330 --> 00:58:28.380
So according to the
theory of advaita,

00:58:28.380 --> 00:58:31.350
when the truth is understood,
then all these things

00:58:31.350 --> 00:58:33.400
do not exist.

00:58:33.400 --> 00:58:37.020
I mean they exist, but
they are not part of it.

00:58:37.020 --> 00:58:38.730
As long as that
is not understood

00:58:38.730 --> 00:58:41.910
you're still in the
circuit, coming,

00:58:41.910 --> 00:58:46.260
going, separate feeling.

00:58:46.260 --> 00:58:47.030
I'm different.

00:58:47.030 --> 00:58:48.266
You're different.

00:58:52.896 --> 00:58:55.100
Look, Shankara is the right--

00:58:55.100 --> 00:58:59.440
is the well-known
interpreter of [INAUDIBLE],,

00:58:59.440 --> 00:59:02.030
advaita philosophy.

00:59:02.030 --> 00:59:06.140
And even after that,
I think he fully

00:59:06.140 --> 00:59:09.980
believed that the mind can be
reborn, come, go, everything,

00:59:09.980 --> 00:59:12.660
even after having
that experience.

00:59:12.660 --> 00:59:18.170
So which means that at
one stage, it is real.

00:59:18.170 --> 00:59:20.900
In another state, it is not.

00:59:20.900 --> 00:59:24.210
From the ultimate point,
there is no such thing.

00:59:27.360 --> 00:59:29.000
OK one more.

00:59:29.000 --> 00:59:31.400
AUDIENCE: Then why do
we have this separation?

00:59:31.400 --> 00:59:33.156
Why are we not born--

00:59:33.156 --> 00:59:35.280
SRI M: I thought he was
going to ask that question.

00:59:35.280 --> 00:59:37.780
AUDIENCE: Yeah, I thought he
was going to ask that question.

00:59:37.780 --> 00:59:41.210
Why are we not born with like--

00:59:41.210 --> 00:59:43.530
SRI M: We don't know.

00:59:43.530 --> 00:59:45.170
But it is so.

00:59:45.170 --> 00:59:47.420
There are many things
which we don't know.

00:59:47.420 --> 00:59:50.810
But it happens to be so.

00:59:50.810 --> 00:59:53.814
And now, since it happens to
be so, how do we get out of it?

00:59:53.814 --> 00:59:54.980
That should be the question.

00:59:57.740 --> 01:00:00.170
Why in the first place
it became like that?

01:00:00.170 --> 01:00:02.630
We have no explanation
for many things

01:00:02.630 --> 01:00:04.430
in the universe that way.

01:00:04.430 --> 01:00:08.070
Perhaps we may
discover at some point.

01:00:08.070 --> 01:00:11.970
If I may say so, all
people who have discovered

01:00:11.970 --> 01:00:15.560
the way, if anybody
has, have not

01:00:15.560 --> 01:00:17.450
been able to explain
it to somebody

01:00:17.450 --> 01:00:18.910
who has not touched it.

01:00:21.820 --> 01:00:24.310
We understand what
I am trying to say?

01:00:24.310 --> 01:00:26.380
You cannot explain it.

01:00:26.380 --> 01:00:27.440
It's not possible.

01:00:27.440 --> 01:00:30.080
It doesn't mean that
you have not found it.

01:00:30.080 --> 01:00:33.190
There are many things which
language and our thought

01:00:33.190 --> 01:00:37.320
process cannot define and catch.

01:00:37.320 --> 01:00:39.780
Those things it is better
leave it like that.

01:00:39.780 --> 01:00:44.280
But the actual fact is
that we are suffering.

01:00:44.280 --> 01:00:46.800
We need to get
out of it somehow.

01:00:46.800 --> 01:00:48.870
Perhaps when we get
out, we find the source

01:00:48.870 --> 01:00:50.130
and why it does happen.

01:00:50.130 --> 01:00:53.520
I'll give you a small
story before we wind up.

01:00:53.520 --> 01:00:56.500
This was Buddha's
very popular story.

01:00:56.500 --> 01:00:59.290
And somebody asked him about the
same thing in a different way.

01:00:59.290 --> 01:01:00.720
Where did the first karma start?

01:01:00.720 --> 01:01:02.460
Why are we going on and on?

01:01:02.460 --> 01:01:03.960
He said, listen.

01:01:03.960 --> 01:01:08.280
You have gone into a
garden to eat fruits.

01:01:08.280 --> 01:01:10.465
Somebody shoots an arrow at you.

01:01:10.465 --> 01:01:14.430
The arrow is stuck in
your chest, there is pain,

01:01:14.430 --> 01:01:16.530
and you might die soon
if you don't pull it

01:01:16.530 --> 01:01:18.290
out and do something about it.

01:01:18.290 --> 01:01:21.060
So the Buddha's question
was, lying down there in pain

01:01:21.060 --> 01:01:24.600
with the arrow in your chest,
what would you do first?

01:01:24.600 --> 01:01:29.130
Would you try to pull it out
and free yourself, and then

01:01:29.130 --> 01:01:31.170
figure out where it came from?

01:01:31.170 --> 01:01:34.320
Or would you lie down there
and say, who sends this arrow,

01:01:34.320 --> 01:01:36.270
where has it come from?

01:01:36.270 --> 01:01:37.590
How do I find the source?

01:01:37.590 --> 01:01:38.760
[LAUGHTER]

01:01:38.760 --> 01:01:39.480
SRI M: You see?

01:01:39.480 --> 01:01:44.220
So in this urgency of
pain, you need to get out.

01:01:44.220 --> 01:01:47.250
Perhaps when you
get out, you might

01:01:47.250 --> 01:01:50.070
be able to go out and see
who has sent this arrow.

01:01:50.070 --> 01:01:52.710
And it may be so
that you may not

01:01:52.710 --> 01:01:54.630
be able to explain it
to the other guy who's

01:01:54.630 --> 01:01:57.880
still laying down with
the arrow in his heart.

01:01:57.880 --> 01:02:01.310
But I'm just trying to give
a theoretical question--

01:02:01.310 --> 01:02:03.930
an answer to a
theoretical question.

01:02:03.930 --> 01:02:06.740
But it comes from
my understanding.

01:02:06.740 --> 01:02:08.787
What's your name?

01:02:08.787 --> 01:02:09.370
AUDIENCE: Raj.

01:02:09.370 --> 01:02:11.290
SRI M: Raj.

01:02:11.290 --> 01:02:12.580
Thank you very much.

01:02:12.580 --> 01:02:13.510
I think now--

01:02:13.510 --> 01:02:15.956
AUDIENCE: Can I-- can I
have one last question?

01:02:15.956 --> 01:02:16.456
[LAUGHTER]

01:02:16.456 --> 01:02:19.410
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

01:02:19.410 --> 01:02:24.430
SRI M: First, are we aware
that the arrow is there?

01:02:24.430 --> 01:02:30.730
Yes, first step is that,
that I feel there pain.

01:02:30.730 --> 01:02:32.620
There is an arrow's [INAUDIBLE].

01:02:32.620 --> 01:02:35.170
Understand this fully first.

01:02:35.170 --> 01:02:37.160
If you understand
this fully, then you

01:02:37.160 --> 01:02:39.700
will find ways to take it out.

01:02:39.700 --> 01:02:42.070
Many people have the arrow,
but they eat lollipops

01:02:42.070 --> 01:02:44.920
and think that it's OK.

01:02:44.920 --> 01:02:47.770
The seriousness of
trying to get out of it

01:02:47.770 --> 01:02:51.850
comes when you really
understand that it is so first.

01:02:51.850 --> 01:02:54.730
Self-realization
does not mean to say

01:02:54.730 --> 01:02:56.410
that I am the Supreme Brahman.

01:02:56.410 --> 01:02:57.370
I'm not this body.

01:02:57.370 --> 01:02:58.570
That's not [INAUDIBLE].

01:02:58.570 --> 01:03:00.610
Self-realization
means to find out

01:03:00.610 --> 01:03:04.610
where I stand at the moment.

01:03:04.610 --> 01:03:07.580
What is life to me?

01:03:07.580 --> 01:03:11.750
Who am I in this context,
not that context?

01:03:11.750 --> 01:03:14.090
When these things
are clear, you'll

01:03:14.090 --> 01:03:19.870
suddenly see a small little
part going to separate it.

01:03:19.870 --> 01:03:22.040
But it must be urgent.

01:03:22.040 --> 01:03:24.620
I really have to get out.

01:03:24.620 --> 01:03:27.830
Till that thing comes,
whatever if I tell you

01:03:27.830 --> 01:03:31.170
the path is not going to work?

01:03:31.170 --> 01:03:33.110
Hm?

01:03:33.110 --> 01:03:36.310
I hope you understood
what I am trying.

01:03:36.310 --> 01:03:37.377
Thank you very much.

01:03:37.377 --> 01:03:38.210
Thank you very much.

01:03:38.210 --> 01:03:40.043
PRASAD SETTY: Thanks
to Sri M, [INAUDIBLE]..

